{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is at module handoff (diff parser -> review-input builder), not a single pure function. REAL-INFRA: no real OS/network/subprocess is required; canned diff payloads are sufficient. LLM-DEP: this behavior checks input scoping, not model judgment. MULTI-STEP: no multi-agent sequence required. Rejection-gate: System is disqualified by behavior text \"scoped to the lines that changed\" (data-shaping invariant, not real transport behavior). Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because the behavior does not require evaluating model output quality.","test_description":"Wire diff ingestion and review-input construction together with realistic unified diffs containing changed and unchanged regions; assert the generated review payload includes only changed-line segments (plus allowed minimal context) and excludes untouched file bodies.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: mapping can look correct internally yet fail against GitHub diff-position semantics. REAL-INFRA: requires real HTTP/API behavior and server-side validation of line/position fields. MOCK-HIDE: mocked API clients can accept invalid mappings that GitHub rejects or remaps. LLM-DEP: not dependent on model quality. MULTI-STEP: not a multi-agent pipeline requirement.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, compute comment positions from the fetched diff and call the real review-comment API; verify each comment appears on the intended file/line in Files Changed (or equivalent API-reported anchor), catching real position/commit-sha mismatches.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: correctness depends on real model judgment (detecting an actual bug), which a stub cannot validate. MOCK-HIDE: deterministic fixtures would always pass/fail based on fixture, hiding true detection quality regressions. REAL-INFRA: external API transport alone is insufficient; core risk is model output quality/non-determinism. MULTI-STEP: this behavior can be satisfied by a single agentic decision, so Workflow is not required. Rejection-gate: Workflow is disqualified because behavior text only requires \"identifies at least one real defect,\" not multiple agentic stages.","test_description":"Run the reviewer with a real model on a seeded PR containing a known bug and assert at least one finding correctly references that defect location/type; execute multiple trials and require a minimum hit rate to account for non-determinism.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to an inline comment that was also posted — no findings appear in the summary without a matching inline comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is cross-module consistency (inline-comment sink -> summary builder), not isolated function logic. REAL-INFRA: can be caught with in-process wiring and recorded posted-comment artifacts; real network is unnecessary. LLM-DEP: behavior is referential integrity between artifacts, not quality of model reasoning. MULTI-STEP: no required multi-agent decision chain. Rejection-gate: Agentic is disqualified by behavior text \"corresponds ... with a matching inline comment\" which defines a deterministic consistency constraint.","test_description":"Use an integration harness with a fake GitHub adapter that records created inline comments; generate the top-level summary from the same run and parse listed findings; assert each summary finding maps to an actually recorded inline comment identifier/location.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — reading the diff, posting inline comments, posting the summary comment — completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"REAL-INFRA: explicitly requires a real pull request and real posting actions (external API). LLM-DEP: pipeline includes automated defect-finding behavior that depends on real model output. MULTI-STEP: this is an end-to-end agent pipeline with sequential stages (read diff -> analyze -> post inline -> post summary), so Workflow is the true failure boundary. Rejection-gate: lower levels are disqualified by behavior text \"full sequence ... for a real pull request without manual intervention,\" which requires end-to-end orchestration.","test_description":"Execute the automation end-to-end on a live test PR with real credentials and real model access; assert each stage succeeds in order, inline comments are created, and the final summary comment is posted and consistent with posted findings, with no human edits or retries outside the automation.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.16,"Workflow":0.62}}]}
